SEVEN people died and many are critically injured, this is after a vehicle overturned on the R56 road between Umzimkhulu and Ixopo in southern KZN on Saturday. According to Umzimkhulu municipality spokesman, Willie Mgcina, none of the people are from the province as the taxi was driving to the Eastern Cape. Mgcina said the information he has received so far indicates that the taxi was from Johannesburg heading to the Eastern Cape, but the accident happened just a few killometres from Umzimkhulu town. Cops spokeswoman, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said the driver of the taxi is among the people who died in the accident. Mbele said a case of culpable homicide was opened at Umzimkhulu police station. She further said the circumstances surrounding the accident are being investigated. 